---
const pillars = [
  {
    t: 'No account',
    b: 'Nothing to sign up for, log into, or get locked out of. Launch, connect a model, work.',
  },
  {
    t: 'No cloud',
    b: 'The agent engine is a local Rust crate. The only network call is the one to your model endpoint.',
  },
  {
    t: 'Any model',
    b: 'Ollama on your GPU, Anthropic or OpenAI by key, or Claude Code on the plan you already pay. Swap live.',
  },
  {
    t: 'Truly open',
    b: 'AGPL-3.0, de-branded, rebrand-friendly, and continuously merged with upstream Warp.',
  },
];
---

<section id="why">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="why-grid">
      <div class="why-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">why uncaged</p>
        <h2 class="section-h">Warp, with the cloud cut out.</h2>
        <p class="section-sub">
          Warp open-sourced its client, but the agent that powers it still runs on Warp's servers —
          behind a login, a subscription, and a relay your prompts and keys pass through. Uncaged
          supplies the missing piece: a small local engine that drives Agent Mode from a backend you
          choose, with the account and paywall gates removed.
        </p>
        <p class="section-sub">
          Same terminal. Same speed. The difference is where the intelligence lives — and who it
          answers to.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="why-diff" role="img" aria-label="The fork summarized as a code diff: Warp's account, cloud relay, telemetry and subscription removed; a local engine, your choice of models, and local keys added">
        <div class="diff-bar">
          <span class="diff-title">the fork, as a diff</span>
          <span class="diff-file">warp → uncaged</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="diff-body"><span class="d-del">-  warp account required for agent mode</span>
<span class="d-del">-  agent requests relayed through warp's cloud</span>
<span class="d-del">-  telemetry, crash reporting, cloud sync</span>
<span class="d-del">-  subscription, credits, request caps</span>
<span class="d-add">+  uncaged_engine — the agent runs on your machine</span>
<span class="d-add">+  your models: local runtime, api key, or cli agent</span>
<span class="d-add">+  your keys, on your disk, nowhere else</span>
<span class="d-add">+  free forever under agpl-3.0</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pillars">
      {
        pillars.map((p, i) => (
          <div class="card">
            <h3>{p.t}</h3>
            <p>{p.b}</p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .why-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 64px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .why-diff {
    background: #0f0c0a;
    border: 1px solid var(--bar);
    border-radius: var(--radius-l);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 18px 50px -20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }

  .diff-bar {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 11px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bar);
    background: rgba(26, 21, 18, 0.6);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11.5px;
  }

  .diff-title {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .diff-file {
    color: #6d6455;
  }

  .diff-body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.9;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .d-del {
    display: block;
    color: #7a705f;
    text-decoration: line-through;
    text-decoration-color: rgba(122, 112, 95, 0.45);
  }

  .d-add {
    display: block;
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .pillars {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 18px;
    margin-top: 72px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .why-grid {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
      gap: 44px;
    }

    .pillars {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .pillars {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
    }
  }
</style>
